parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty wiring can cause a loud buzzing noise, which can be a distraction to the driver, and potentially lead to an electrical fire or other safety issues.
symptoms: Loud buzzing noise when moving the turn signal stem
noise increases in frequency and volume over time
noise becomes constant even when the turn signal is not engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to roll down unexpectedly, which can lead to theft, water damage, or other safety issues.
symptoms: Power window will not roll up
window rolls down by itself
possible shorting out of the electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Electrical fire
smoke or burning smell from the electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Rod Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine rod can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing a vehicle fire, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The engine suddenly fails or seizes
the vehicle loses power
the engine makes loud knocking or grinding noises
the vehicle is unable to move
smoke or flames emanate from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can result in serious injury or death, and can also cause significant damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: Smoke or flames emanate from the engine compartment
the vehicle is engulfed in flames
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle's interior is damaged by fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer cable assembly can cause the speedometer to malfunction, leading to inaccurate speed readings, which can affect vehicle safety and performance. The loud screeching noise caused by the stuck cable head can also be a distraction to the driver.
symptoms: The speedometer cable assembly makes noise
the speedometer is frozen
the speedometer is inaccurate
loud screeching noise at speeds over 20 mph
stuck cable head.
